37
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:57,970
She told us that she's going to the restroom around...3:30am.

38
00:01:57,970 --> 00:02:02,100
We started looking
for her around 4...right?

39
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:02,890
Huh?

40
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:06,830
I think so.

41
00:02:07,740 --> 00:02:10,790
Oh no, oh no!
I have to go and make breakfast.

42
00:02:11,830 --> 00:02:12,750
I see.

43
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:13,800
Let's talk outside.

44
00:02:17,670 --> 00:02:20,080
Is she going to be okay?

45
00:02:21,050 --> 00:02:24,970
Maybe she ran away,
maybe she didn't.

46
00:02:24,970 --> 00:02:28,010
Well, I can't tell you anything as of now.

47
00:02:28,980 --> 00:02:32,970
Did you all see the
pervert from the restroom?

48
00:02:32,970 --> 00:02:34,940
No, only one person did.

49
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:41,100
I saw him too.

50
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:42,700
I remember how he looks like.

51
00:02:43,020 --> 00:02:46,110
I need your info.

52
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:48,000
Your names, addresses...

53
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:51,090
No! I can't give it to you!

54
00:02:52,740 --> 00:02:54,130
I don't want someone to find me!

55
00:02:54,130 --> 00:02:55,830
Give it to me.

56
00:02:55,830 --> 00:02:57,770
We need it for the missing person.

57
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:02,660
Don't worry,
we won't disclose it to anyone.

58
00:03:02,660 --> 00:03:05,710
Officer, Su-Duk needs to go
and make breakfast.

59
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:07,020
Let us go, please?

60
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:10,090
We need to go home as soon as we can.
We can't be late.

61
00:03:11,090 --> 00:03:16,110
I see, but we need one person
to come to the station with us.

62
00:03:17,970 --> 00:03:19,760
I'll stay.

63
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,680
Okay, you can come with me.

64
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:24,690
The rest of you can leave after
giving us your numbers and addresses.

65
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:17,090
Im Tae-Ran! You're so lucky!

66
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:18,950
You have everything!

67
00:04:20,910 --> 00:04:21,970
Are you okay?

68
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:27,090
Don't worry, I can swim my way out
even if I fell into a jar of liquor.

69
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:29,880
You're not the only one
having a tough time.

70
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:35,900
Who else is having a tough time? You?

71
00:04:35,910 --> 00:04:37,820
Kang Jin dumped me.

72
00:04:39,910 --> 00:04:42,690
We've been going out for over a year,
but he didn't say anything.

73
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:44,970
So I proposed to him first.

74
00:04:44,980 --> 00:04:45,940
And?

75
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:57,860
He said he likes me, and that
I'm perfect, except...I'm too old.

76
00:04:57,860 --> 00:05:01,920
What a dimwit!

77
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:04,720
He's the same age as you, right?

78
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:11,150
That kid doesn't know anything.

79
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:21,070
Tae-Ran, you're the kind of girl
a man should marry.

80
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,080
Look at me!

81
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:31,070
Look what happened to me because
I didn't marry someone like you!

82
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:42,780
I should've married you when
you told me that you like me.

83
00:05:43,780 --> 00:05:44,910
Don't you think so?

84
00:05:46,990 --> 00:05:49,880
I should've married you instead!

85
00:06:07,660 --> 00:06:08,800
Myung-Pil...

86
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:16,810
Myung-Pil! That hurts...

87
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:19,000
Tae-Ran, are you okay?

88
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,900
Myung-Pil, where are we?

89
00:06:24,860 --> 00:06:26,900
You're heavy.

90
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:37,800
Myung-Pil...

91
00:06:38,710 --> 00:06:39,760
Tae-Ran!

92
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:50,760
Myung-Pil!

93
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,110
I have to go. I have a meeting to attend.

94
00:08:16,050 --> 00:08:17,870
Why is there so much traffic?

95
00:08:17,870 --> 00:08:20,020
Hurry!

96
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:21,800
What are we going to do?

97
00:08:21,810 --> 00:08:24,780
Be quiet, will you?

98
00:08:24,790 --> 00:08:27,080
You have nothing to worry about because you don't have a husband.

99
00:08:27,930 --> 00:08:30,670
Are you bragging that
you have husband?

100
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:32,080
What are we going to do?

101
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:34,130
If this is a dream, please wake me up.

102
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:35,790
Oh, no!

103
00:08:35,790 --> 00:08:37,680
It's morning, and this isn't a dream.

104
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:39,920
I can't believe I didn't
go home last night.

105
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:41,150
Me too!

106
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:43,770
My husband should
be back from his shift.

107
00:08:43,770 --> 00:08:46,130
I'm so dead!

108
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:48,060
I hate people who bring
trouble upon others!

109
00:08:49,870 --> 00:08:51,770
Oh, no...

110
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:52,930
Lord, what should I do?

111
00:08:52,930 --> 00:08:56,960
My pass! My pass!
Be quiet, will you?

112
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,910
Please let me make
breakfast for my kids.

113
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:00,850
My husband didn't call.

114
00:09:00,850 --> 00:09:03,940
My husband didn't call either! How come you didn't remember to bring your pass?

115
00:09:03,940 --> 00:09:06,820
Ah!! Be quiet!! Quiet!!

116
00:09:06,820 --> 00:09:08,890
What are we going to do?

117
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,110
Hurry up!

118
00:09:15,110 --> 00:09:16,950
Be quiet!

119
00:09:18,740 --> 00:09:21,780
Were you worried about me?

120
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:26,750
I had a few drinks because
I was in a bad mood.

121
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:30,730
I found myself at the bar in the morning.

122
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:35,040
Things like this happen when men drink!

123
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:40,840
I wonder if she'll buy that.

124
00:09:43,010 --> 00:09:45,070
She has no choice!

125
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:48,720
She didn't see what happened last night!

126
00:09:53,010 --> 00:09:54,100
This is driving me crazy...

127
00:10:03,930 --> 00:10:07,750
Honey, I went to the beach
because I was in a bad mood.

128
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,880
No, no... Honey...

129
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:11,800
I'm sorry, please forgive me.

130
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,740
This is the first time
I stayed out until morning!

131
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:14,130
Honey...

132
00:10:14,130 --> 00:10:14,920
No.

133
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:15,900
Please forgive me, honey.

134
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:17,070
I'll do anything you say.

135
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:21,850
I shouldn't have had
that cocktail last night...

136
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:28,950
Honey...

137
00:10:30,810 --> 00:10:31,920
Ho...honey...

138
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:45,080
Why is she here?

139
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:47,030
Was she waiting for me?

140
00:10:47,030 --> 00:10:49,060
He's here to get me.

141
00:10:49,060 --> 00:10:50,930
What am I going to do?

142
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,040
This is driving me crazy.

143
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,840
What am I going to do?

144
00:11:11,850 --> 00:11:13,100
Why isn't she saying anything?

145
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:16,870
I didn't come home last night.

146
00:11:16,870 --> 00:11:18,910
I thought he'd say something about it.

147
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,850
Mom!

148
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:28,750
Did you decide to get
on my bad side for good?

149
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:31,990
Did you guys go for a walk...

150
00:11:31,990 --> 00:11:35,780
...after making your old
mother-in-law take care of the kids?

151
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:36,770
- Mother..
- Mom..

152
00:11:36,770 --> 00:11:39,940
I sent Eun-Suk to school.

153
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:42,890
He wants his art homework.

154
00:11:43,730 --> 00:11:44,060
Okay.

155
00:11:45,050 --> 00:11:45,840
B...B..Bye.

156
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,840
Bye, Grandma!

157
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,740
By the way!

158
00:11:51,790 --> 00:11:55,670
You have to get Grandfather's
memorial from his brother's house.

159
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:58,880
But the house is a little too small...

160
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:04,770
I was going to let you bring it
after you buy a house...

161
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:08,130
...but I don't know
when that's going to be.

162
00:12:10,790 --> 00:12:13,730
Let's get the dishes
for the service for now.

163
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:14,970
Okay.

164
00:12:14,970 --> 00:12:16,800
Goodbye, Grandma.

165
00:12:34,710 --> 00:12:35,690
Are you hungry?

166
00:12:35,690 --> 00:12:36,730
Huh?

167
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:38,030
Uh...yes.

168
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:41,060
That's weird.

169
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:43,910
Why isn't she doing anything?

170
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:46,130
Maybe she doesn't know that
I didn't come home last night.

171
00:12:46,130 --> 00:12:48,980
He doesn't look mad.

172
00:12:48,980 --> 00:12:50,760
Maybe he doesn't know that
I didn't come home last night.

173
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,070
Did she go to bed early?

174
00:12:53,890 --> 00:12:56,910
Maybe he was too drunk to remember.

175
00:12:59,810 --> 00:13:01,680
I'll make you breakfast.

176
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:02,780
Okay...

177
00:13:04,970 --> 00:13:06,720
Honey!

178
00:13:10,860 --> 00:13:14,150
When did you sleep last night?

179
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,670
Huh?

180
00:13:18,110 --> 00:13:23,950
Uh...I was too drunk last night.

181
00:13:24,850 --> 00:13:27,020
I can't remember anything.

182
00:13:29,050 --> 00:13:30,940
You can't remember anything?

183
00:13:30,940 --> 00:13:33,070
No...I can't.

184
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:39,070
Oh...I see...

185
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:45,050
I went to bed early last night
because I was tired.

186
00:13:45,050 --> 00:13:48,110
I feel asleep in Eun-Suk's room.

187
00:13:48,110 --> 00:13:51,730
I was lost in thought in
Euk-Suk's room, and fell asleep.

188
00:13:52,910 --> 00:13:54,910
I see!

189
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:56,860
I came home drunk last night.

190
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:59,720
When I woke up, I found myself
in the computer room!

191
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:01,800
So that's why you didn't see me.

192
00:14:02,110 --> 00:14:03,860
I see!

193
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:07,060
You look tired.

194
00:14:07,070 --> 00:14:08,750
You must've had a lot to drink.

195
00:14:09,140 --> 00:14:12,760
Yes, I drank more than I should!

196
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:16,120
You look tired too.

197
00:14:16,130 --> 00:14:17,840
I guess you didn't get
much sleep last night.

198
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:20,150
You're right.

199
00:14:21,980 --> 00:14:24,020
I'll make you breakfast.

200
00:14:24,020 --> 00:14:26,990
Good, I need it to relieve my hangover.

201
00:14:39,110 --> 00:14:39,950
Gi-Suk.

202
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:41,980
Behave, okay?

203
00:14:41,990 --> 00:14:43,660
Okay.

204
00:14:43,670 --> 00:14:44,790
Bye.

205
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:56,680
What happened?

206
00:14:58,860 --> 00:15:00,130
He must've thrown a fit.

207
00:15:01,660 --> 00:15:02,930
You didn't tell him about me, right?

208
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:06,090
He doesn't know
that I didn't come home.

209
00:15:06,090 --> 00:15:08,060
He was too drunk last night
and couldn't remember.

210
00:15:09,140 --> 00:15:10,930
Good.

211
00:15:13,110 --> 00:15:14,880
Su-Duk!

212
00:15:18,010 --> 00:15:19,980
Are you okay?

213
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:26,710
Oh, no...

214
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:32,070
My husband threw a spoon at me.

215
00:15:32,070 --> 00:15:35,080
He's the pitcher for the
neighborhood baseball team.

216
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:36,960
I'm grounded now.

217
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:40,130
He said he'll throw the rice cooker at me if I leave home without permission.

218
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:42,090
What are you doing here?

219
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:47,000
I'll be fine as long as I'm within 100m.

220
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,700
I can answer the phone
and pretend I'm home.

221
00:15:49,060 --> 00:15:49,990
I'm sorry.

222
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:52,100
It was my idea to go to the beach.

223
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:57,940
I'm glad I divorced.

224
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:10,090
Her family must be worried about her.

225
00:16:10,930 --> 00:16:14,940
They must be wondering
if she's dead or alive.

226
00:16:15,890 --> 00:16:17,770
I'm sure they called the cops.

227
00:16:20,130 --> 00:16:21,720
Is Yun-Shil back?

228
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:22,870
I think so.

229
00:16:22,890 --> 00:16:23,830
Wait.

230
00:16:36,990 --> 00:16:38,000
Hello?

231
00:16:46,710 --> 00:16:48,950
Her husband looks like a nice person.

232
00:16:51,660 --> 00:16:54,100
The Police took Yun-Shil's cell phone.

233
00:16:56,050 --> 00:16:58,080
They said no one called her.

234
00:16:59,110 --> 00:17:02,080
Then...why does he look so nonchalant?

235
00:17:02,830 --> 00:17:04,710
Maybe she called.

236
00:17:04,730 --> 00:17:07,820
Maybe she called her family.

237
00:17:07,820 --> 00:17:08,900
Maybe.

238
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:12,850
Shall we ask her husband if she called?

239
00:17:12,850 --> 00:17:13,900
What if she didn't?

240
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:15,870
He'll tell us to do something about it.

241
00:17:15,870 --> 00:17:18,130
I hate getting myself into
someone else's business.

242
00:17:18,850 --> 00:17:20,830
Are you telling us that
we should do nothing?

243
00:17:20,830 --> 00:17:22,870
The cops told us not to talk about it.

244
00:17:22,890 --> 00:17:26,730
If she ran away,
then what we say can wreck a home.

245
00:17:33,970 --> 00:17:35,760
What's this?

246
00:17:35,770 --> 00:17:37,830
Look who we have here.

247
00:17:38,870 --> 00:17:41,090
Birds of the same feather flock together.

248
00:17:42,710 --> 00:17:44,660
You guys split last night
without cleaning up, right?

249
00:17:44,660 --> 00:17:45,060
Split?

250
00:17:45,060 --> 00:17:46,740
Come on.

251
00:17:47,090 --> 00:17:48,870
We're all neighbors here.

252
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:51,850
Let's be nice to each other.

253
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,030
I don't think of you as my neighbor.

254
00:17:54,030 --> 00:17:55,760
Me neither.

255
00:17:57,870 --> 00:17:59,150
Where we you last night?

256
00:17:59,150 --> 00:18:01,110
None of you guys picked up
your interphones.

257
00:18:01,930 --> 00:18:03,960
I don't have to tell you that.

258
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:06,010
You're not the Police.

259
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:09,890
Look at these fatheads!

260
00:18:09,890 --> 00:18:12,810
How dare you talk back to me
when you split without cleaning up?

261
00:18:12,810 --> 00:18:14,780
Ooh, I'm scared.

262
00:18:14,780 --> 00:18:16,150
I know...

263
00:18:17,660 --> 00:18:20,800
I'll clean it like you say
by the end of this week.

264
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:21,730
So...

265
00:18:21,730 --> 00:18:23,700
What do you take me for?

266
00:18:24,060 --> 00:18:28,820
Sure, I'll show you what
it means to mess with me.

267
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:42,790
Choi! Kim! What's with the long faces?

268
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:46,090
You guys look like miserable
white-collar workers.

269
00:18:48,860 --> 00:18:49,930
You're going to get wrinkles
on your forehead.

270
00:18:49,930 --> 00:18:53,800
Smile, life's not too bad, right?

271
00:18:53,810 --> 00:18:55,040
Are you happy about something?

272
00:18:56,790 --> 00:18:58,050
Can you tell?

