serious if they hear this.

289
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,790
It's just between us.

290
00:20:34,980 --> 00:20:36,680
What is it?

291
00:20:40,710 --> 00:20:45,890
What happens if she doesn't call
after a one-night stand?

292
00:20:47,710 --> 00:20:51,150
One night stand means
it's just for one night.

293
00:20:52,090 --> 00:20:56,080
You're not supposed to call
the other person the next day.

294
00:20:57,840 --> 00:20:59,910
She left a note saying she's leaving.

295
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:03,000
They both know each other's numbers.

296
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,800
She can text him, right?

297
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:07,020
That means she has come to her senses.

298
00:21:07,020 --> 00:21:08,770
She's disappointed in the guy.

299
00:21:12,090 --> 00:21:13,780
Forget about it.

300
00:21:13,780 --> 00:21:17,890
You're supposed to forget about one-night stands after the night is over.

301
00:21:21,740 --> 00:21:23,000
What if she's someone I know?

302
00:21:27,710 --> 00:21:34,670
That's the worst one-night stand
out of them all!

303
00:21:34,670 --> 00:21:36,740
You'll only get yourself embarrassed
and lose a friend!

304
00:21:36,740 --> 00:21:38,930
You have nothing to gain!

305
00:21:44,790 --> 00:21:45,990
Don't worry.

306
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:49,870
Just take it one step at a time.

307
00:21:49,870 --> 00:21:53,750
If you want to continue the relationship, you can be her boyfriend.

308
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:55,730
If you regret what you've done...

309
00:21:55,730 --> 00:22:02,690
...forget about the one-night stand and pretend as if nothing has happened.

310
00:22:19,660 --> 00:22:22,130
I guess I had too much to drink...

311
00:22:34,730 --> 00:22:41,130
Tears aren't the only things
a man shouldn't spill.

312
00:22:51,710 --> 00:22:54,820
I'm getting the memorial dishes from your brother's house.

313
00:22:54,820 --> 00:22:56,780
Can you come and help me carry them?

314
00:23:03,720 --> 00:23:06,040
We should've taken
them a long time ago.

315
00:23:06,040 --> 00:23:08,030
Thanks for taking care of them.

316
00:23:08,030 --> 00:23:09,890
You're welcome.

317
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:12,670
I'm busy.

318
00:23:19,750 --> 00:23:21,850
Sheesh...

319
00:23:21,850 --> 00:23:25,690
Myung-Pil, I'm at a cafe
near your workplace.

320
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,730
Yes!

321
00:23:59,670 --> 00:24:02,150
Persistence is the key.

322
00:24:02,150 --> 00:24:03,800
I called after getting tired of texting.

323
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:04,960
She answered the phone!

324
00:24:05,890 --> 00:24:08,990
I was having an interview
nearby when he called.

325
00:24:08,990 --> 00:24:10,130
What's this?

326
00:24:10,130 --> 00:24:11,700
She's too nonchalant.

327
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:13,780
And I'm sure you know that
love is all about timing.

328
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:15,110
You should be a writer.

329
00:24:15,110 --> 00:24:18,080
It'll be a waste to use your lines
for hitting on girls only.

330
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,660
What?

331
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:21,900
Maybe she doesn't remember.

332
00:24:24,070 --> 00:24:26,050
Myung-Pil, stop him!

333
00:24:26,050 --> 00:24:28,710
Huh? Okay...

334
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:35,950
If you regret what you've done, forget about the one-night stand and...

335
00:24:35,950 --> 00:24:40,690
...pretend as of nothing has happened.

336
00:24:44,910 --> 00:24:45,970
Choi!

337
00:24:46,840 --> 00:24:48,860
