476
00:34:24,060 --> 00:34:25,680
- Good evening!
- Good evening!

477
00:34:25,680 --> 00:34:27,750
Hi.

478
00:34:27,750 --> 00:34:29,110
The fruit punch is good.

479
00:34:29,110 --> 00:34:30,930
Myung-Pil's sister will love it.

480
00:34:30,930 --> 00:34:33,890
The rice punch I made for you
doesn't have any sugar.

481
00:34:33,890 --> 00:34:35,060
Attention, everyone.

482
00:34:35,060 --> 00:34:37,910
I have two announcements to make.

483
00:34:37,910 --> 00:34:42,700
First, we're not going to discuss remodeling our villa anymore.

484
00:34:43,090 --> 00:34:48,800
Remodeling? That's for
the homeowners to worry about.

485
00:34:49,150 --> 00:34:57,740
The second one is about the women
who threw away their trash illegally.

486
00:34:58,670 --> 00:35:01,120
I'm sure you are all aware they were punished with cleaning up the trash bin.

487
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:06,790
But these 4 housewives
instead went to the beach...

488
00:35:06,790 --> 00:35:08,140
...and didn't come home that night.

489
00:35:13,060 --> 00:35:18,890
I ask the other residents
to please refrain yourselves...

490
00:35:18,890 --> 00:35:21,670
...from embarrassing the
other good residents here.

491
00:35:22,780 --> 00:35:24,740
This was your head of the
neighborhood association speaking.

492
00:35:31,910 --> 00:35:33,680
Is she talking about you?

493
00:35:34,880 --> 00:35:37,810
You didn't come home last night?

494
00:35:38,110 --> 00:35:39,910
Did you go to the beach?

495
00:35:40,690 --> 00:35:42,730
You didn't come home?

496
00:35:42,740 --> 00:35:44,050
Oh, my...

497
00:35:44,990 --> 00:35:48,950
I had a good reason.

498
00:35:48,950 --> 00:35:51,110
You see...

499
00:35:51,120 --> 00:35:55,870
We just went there
for some fresh air, but...

500
00:35:55,870 --> 00:35:57,750
You didn't come home?

501
00:35:57,750 --> 00:36:00,670
Does this mean you were
on your way home...

502
00:36:00,670 --> 00:36:02,800
...when you met me
in front of the house?

503
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:15,060
How can you dare leave your kids
home and stay out for the night?

504
00:36:15,060 --> 00:36:16,940
The end is near.

505
00:36:16,940 --> 00:36:17,880
Oh, Lord...

506
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:19,790
You must be out of your mind!

507
00:36:19,790 --> 00:36:20,800
You're crazy!

508
00:36:23,760 --> 00:36:26,990
How embarrassing!

509
00:36:26,990 --> 00:36:28,840
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

510
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,150
I'm sorry, Honey.

511
00:36:30,150 --> 00:36:32,790
I only wanted some fresh air.

512
00:36:32,790 --> 00:36:34,800
I wasn't planning on spending the night.

513
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:35,150
Let's go.

514
00:36:35,150 --> 00:36:37,840
I'll explain everything at home.

515
00:36:37,840 --> 00:36:39,020
I don't want to hear it!

516
00:36:39,020 --> 00:36:41,780
Not even your husband
stays out for the night!

517
00:36:44,140 --> 00:36:46,920
Everyone's good at something.

518
00:36:46,930 --> 00:36:51,050
I guess you're good
at ditching your family!

519
00:36:51,050 --> 00:36:52,790
This is so embarrassing.

520
00:36:52,790 --> 00:36:54,920
I don't think I can come back
to this neighborhood again.

521
00:36:56,010 --> 00:36:56,870
Mother...

522
00:36:56,870 --> 00:36:57,900
Mom...

523
00:37:00,790 --> 00:37:02,140
How can you...

524
00:37:05,080 --> 00:37:06,680
Honey...

525
00:37:08,820 --> 00:37:09,990
Honey!

526
00:37:13,730 --> 00:37:15,140
You're already giving me
enough trouble as it is.

527
00:37:15,140 --> 00:37:16,670
And now this?

528
00:37:18,020 --> 00:37:22,720
Yesterday was a tough day for me to.

529
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:23,970
Tough?

530
00:37:24,860 --> 00:37:27,660
I worked hard to make
money for my family...

531
00:37:27,660 --> 00:37:30,850
...but my wife screwed up
and lost a house!

532
00:37:30,850 --> 00:37:32,050
How about me?

533
00:37:32,890 --> 00:37:35,850
Why did you go to the beach?

534
00:37:36,680 --> 00:37:39,040
A woman doesn't have a reason
not to come home.

535
00:37:40,700 --> 00:37:42,700
Okay, I'm sorry.

536
00:37:44,020 --> 00:37:45,730
You know what camels are, right?

537
00:37:46,110 --> 00:37:49,940
Do you know how camels can
withstand the desert for a week?

538
00:37:50,710 --> 00:37:53,710
They can store 100 liters of water
in less than 10 minutes.

539
00:37:53,710 --> 00:37:55,990
That's what keeps them alive.

540
00:37:55,990 --> 00:37:59,150
Do you know where you get
your 100 liters of water?

541
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:00,970
It's me!

542
00:38:00,970 --> 00:38:03,960
I'm the one who teaches you
and scolds you!

543
00:38:04,730 --> 00:38:06,680
This is what gets me!

544
00:38:06,680 --> 00:38:09,680
Why do I always have to be
disappointed and mad at you?

545
00:38:14,860 --> 00:38:15,830
I'm sorry.

546
00:38:18,660 --> 00:38:19,740
Be quiet!

547
00:38:35,130 --> 00:38:38,910
Tae-Ran, I'm so frustrated.

548
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:52,920
What's wrong?

549
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,710
What happened?

550
00:38:54,710 --> 00:38:55,990
Do you want to meet up?

551
00:39:04,100 --> 00:39:06,800
Honey...

552
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:08,870
Honey, where are you going?

553
00:39:28,850 --> 00:39:30,740
Here, is this the man?

554
00:39:32,890 --> 00:39:35,720
Yes, he's the pervert I saw at the beach.

555
00:39:37,070 --> 00:39:39,040
That's odd.

556
00:39:40,910 --> 00:39:43,930
He doesn't have anything to do
with Lee Yun-Shil.

557
00:39:44,980 --> 00:39:47,820
He was caught drunk driving.

558
00:39:47,820 --> 00:39:52,690
He's been at the station
ever since he was arrested at 2am.

559
00:39:52,690 --> 00:39:54,780
Lee Yun-Shil was missing since 4am.

560
00:40:32,820 --> 00:40:33,960
Are you okay?

561
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:36,940
Are you sick?

562
00:40:36,940 --> 00:40:39,730
What 's wrong with my life, Tae-Ran?

563
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:45,890
Everyday is a battle.

564
00:40:47,100 --> 00:40:54,040
Think of how tough it is
for a weakling like me.

565
00:40:55,730 --> 00:40:56,780
What's wrong?

566
00:40:57,860 --> 00:40:59,810
You seem to be having
a lot of trouble too.

567
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:05,700
I get depressed whenever I stay
in that workroom by myself.

568
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:08,990
Looking out the window...

569
00:41:08,990 --> 00:41:12,850
...made me think about the people...

570
00:41:12,850 --> 00:41:15,750
...who committed suicide
out of loneliness out of loneliness.

571
00:41:15,750 --> 00:41:17,980
My eyes started watering up.

572
00:41:32,790 --> 00:41:34,050
Your husband left?

573
00:41:36,050 --> 00:41:38,020
It's because of the neighborhood association lady, right?

574
00:41:38,990 --> 00:41:42,140
I can't believe she announced that!

575
00:41:42,140 --> 00:41:43,970
She has a family too.

576
00:41:49,930 --> 00:41:52,660
Oh, and about Yun-Shil.

577
00:41:53,770 --> 00:41:55,030
He said it's probably not a criminal case.

578
00:41:55,030 --> 00:41:56,680
He wants us to wait.

579
00:42:03,670 --> 00:42:06,020
I'm sorry for making you go
to the station by yourself.

580
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:11,990
I don't know what's wrong with my life.

581
00:42:11,990 --> 00:42:14,970
It's one battle after another.

582
00:42:35,670 --> 00:42:36,760
Honey...

583
00:42:37,770 --> 00:42:38,970
Honey...

584
00:42:58,990 --> 00:43:00,080
I'm tired.

585
00:43:00,090 --> 00:43:01,150
I don't want to talk.

586
00:43:04,960 --> 00:43:14,730
I'm sorry about not coming home
last night, but I had a reason.

587
00:43:17,710 --> 00:43:20,120
I heard your conversation with Tae-Ran.

588
00:43:20,950 --> 00:43:23,070
You told her that you should've
married her instead.

589
00:43:25,990 --> 00:43:30,780
I'm trying to be a good wife.

590
00:43:30,780 --> 00:43:32,860
I'm not always smiling
because I'm happy.

591
00:43:32,860 --> 00:43:37,880
It's tough for me too, but I'm trying
to act cheerful for my family's sake.

592
00:43:37,880 --> 00:43:42,710
How can you say that to me?

593
00:43:44,870 --> 00:43:48,020
I couldn't help myself
after hearing that, so I left.

594
00:43:49,070 --> 00:43:50,150
I just left.

595
00:43:50,150 --> 00:43:53,130
If I didn't...I thought
my head would burst.

596
00:44:00,770 --> 00:44:03,710
It was because of Tae-Ran?

597
00:44:03,710 --> 00:44:05,900
Did you get Botox on your brain again?

598
00:44:05,910 --> 00:44:08,670
I told you to use your brain!

599
00:44:09,900 --> 00:44:12,770
Why do you think I said that to Tae-Ran?

600
00:44:12,770 --> 00:44:15,030
I only said it because
she's better than you are.

601
00:44:15,030 --> 00:44:18,720
She bought two houses,
but you lost a house.

602
00:44:19,690 --> 00:44:24,050
Don't make me feed the need
to say something like that!

603
00:44:24,060 --> 00:44:27,040
Just become a better woman
than Tae-Ran is!

604
00:44:28,050 --> 00:44:30,120
How can you say that?

605
00:44:30,960 --> 00:44:32,020
Because she's better than you!

606
00:44:32,020 --> 00:44:33,740
Because it's true!

607
00:44:36,010 --> 00:44:38,730
A good wife?
And a good mother?

608
00:44:39,080 --> 00:44:41,070
Not everyone can be a good wife!

609
00:44:41,890 --> 00:44:43,880
Especially if you don't
come home for the night!

610
00:44:45,040 --> 00:44:48,840
You're not qualified to be a good wife!

611
00:44:48,840 --> 00:44:52,120
Those pathetic women
are all disqualified!

612
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:53,130
All of them!

613
00:44:56,900 --> 00:44:59,760
Don't ever hang out with those
pathetic women again, okay?

614
00:45:00,140 --> 00:45:02,950
I'm not going to talk to you
if I see you with them again!

615
00:45:04,660 --> 00:45:05,710
Got that?

616
00:45:06,700 --> 00:45:07,800
Got it.

617
00:45:30,020 --> 00:45:33,080
Your wisdom tooth will
hurt more under stress.

618
00:45:33,080 --> 00:45:34,980
You're stressed out because
you fought with your husband.

619
00:45:45,890 --> 00:45:47,770
Honey, it's me.

620
00:45:48,130 --> 00:45:50,790
Don't skip lunch...

621
00:46:09,820 --> 00:46:11,070
Jang-Mi?

622
00:46:18,770 --> 00:46:21,000
Is Yun-Shil's husband back yet?

623
00:46:22,140 --> 00:46:23,720
There he is.

624
00:46:37,900 --> 00:46:41,930
You didn't have to come.

625
00:46:41,930 --> 00:46:44,700
I heard what happened from the Police.

626
00:46:44,700 --> 00:46:45,870
Oh, so you heard.

627
00:46:45,870 --> 00:46:47,790
You must've been shocked.

628
00:46:47,790 --> 00:46:49,110
She'll be fine.

629
00:46:49,110 --> 00:46:54,990
I think she decided to go on a trip
after a visit to the beach.

630
00:46:55,000 --> 00:46:57,960
People sometimes want
to get away from everything.

631
00:46:59,040 --> 00:47:00,760
I'm sure she'll call soon.

632
00:47:00,760 --> 00:47:02,090
You're not even mad.

633
00:47:02,090 --> 00:47:03,860
I was expecting you to yell at us.

634
00:47:04,940 --> 00:47:06,060
Why would I be mad?

635
00:47:06,060 --> 00:47:09,030
My wife always talked about
how much she misses the beach.

636
00:47:09,040 --> 00:47:12,720
Let's wait for her.

637
00:47:13,150 --> 00:47:16,100
Good things happen to people
who think positively.

638
00:47:16,100 --> 00:47:17,870
You know that, right?

639
00:47:25,850 --> 00:47:27,880
Yun-Shil is so lucky.

640
00:47:27,880 --> 00:47:30,100
He's a gentleman.

641
00:47:35,690 --> 00:47:36,810
What's wrong?

642
00:47:36,810 --> 00:47:38,730
Well...

643
00:47:38,730 --> 00:47:40,890
I don't think he's a good person.

644
00:47:41,940 --> 00:47:43,070
Look at his pants.

645
00:47:43,070 --> 00:47:47,120
He's wearing white linen
pants on a rainy day.

646
00:47:47,120 --> 00:47:48,960
Those pants will be ruined.

647
00:47:48,960 --> 00:47:50,850
You're right.

648
00:47:50,850 --> 00:47:52,750
He's stylish.

649
00:47:53,730 --> 00:47:57,680
Yun-Shil has two kids and
works at a bank, right?

650
00:47:58,670 --> 00:48:00,000
She must've been busy working
and taking care of her kids...

651
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:03,860
...and her stylish husband.

652
00:48:05,110 --> 00:48:08,870
All families give the woman a hard time.

653
00:48:29,870 --> 00:48:32,680
She must be a good friend.

654
00:48:32,680 --> 00:48:34,940
You're very concerned about her article.

655
00:48:34,940 --> 00:48:37,010
She's my friend,
but she's good enough to be...

656
00:48:37,010 --> 00:48:41,830
...one of the 10 best writers
in Korean cinema.

657
00:48:42,840 --> 00:48:44,050
If you write a good article about her...

658
00:48:44,050 --> 00:48:46,720
...I'll arrange an interview with
Yoon Jenma for you.

659
00:48:46,720 --> 00:48:47,760
Really?

660
00:48:47,760 --> 00:48:49,060
That's a promise!

661
00:49:02,830 --> 00:49:04,740
Don't wear knockoffs.

662
00:49:04,740 --> 00:49:06,900
You should wear designer's clothing.

663
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:09,690
I'm only going to buy you the real stuff.

664
00:49:11,120 --> 00:49:13,920
I don't mind knockoffs
as long as they're from you.

665
00:49:15,940 --> 00:49:16,930
Let's sit down.

666
00:49:25,040 --> 00:49:29,020
Why don't we go on a trip when
you're done with the screenplay?

667
00:49:29,020 --> 00:49:30,700
Just the two of us.

668
00:49:30,700 --> 00:49:32,790
Sounds great.

669
00:49:33,110 --> 00:49:37,750
But I don't know when I'll be done.

670
00:49:38,830 --> 00:49:39,940
Do you have writer's block?

671
00:49:40,890 --> 00:49:42,020
This is driving me crazy.

672
00:49:42,020 --> 00:49:44,710
All I need is a lead,
but I can't seem to find it.

673
00:49:48,150 --> 00:49:50,960
Why don't you work somewhere else?

674
00:49:50,960 --> 00:49:53,950
It'll help if you change your setting.

675
00:49:55,760 --> 00:49:56,990
Why don't you go to Yangpyeong?

676
00:49:56,990 --> 00:49:58,670
You can rent a cottage.

677
00:49:58,670 --> 00:50:00,080
A cottage by myself?

678
00:50:00,090 --> 00:50:01,750
Sounds horrible.

679
00:50:01,750 --> 00:50:03,150
You won't be alone.

680
00:50:03,150 --> 00:50:04,710
I'll be with you.

681
00:50:05,870 --> 00:50:06,960
Do you want to go today?

682
00:50:06,960 --> 00:50:08,740
Let's look for a good cottage
for you to write in.

683
00:50:09,690 --> 00:50:10,800
Really?

684
00:50:25,060 --> 00:50:26,150
Hello?

685
00:50:28,110 --> 00:50:29,880
The police station?

686
00:50:33,720 --> 00:50:35,870
I hope they found Yun-Shil.

687
00:50:35,870 --> 00:50:36,920
I hope so too.

688
00:50:36,920 --> 00:50:38,820
I don't believe this.

689
00:50:38,830 --> 00:50:41,720
How many times do I have
to go to the police station?

690
00:50:41,720 --> 00:50:44,020
I hate getting myself into
someone else's business.

691
00:50:47,710 --> 00:50:49,120
Are you going to the station?

692
00:50:49,120 --> 00:50:51,710
Get in, I'm going to the station too.

693
00:50:57,970 --> 00:51:00,860
I don't believe this.

694
00:51:00,860 --> 00:51:02,680
What's the matter?

695
00:51:02,690 --> 00:51:04,720
She called in the afternoon.

696
00:51:04,730 --> 00:51:07,000
She's nonchalant about everything.

697
00:51:08,830 --> 00:51:09,950
Where did she go?

698
00:51:09,950 --> 00:51:11,730
Why did she leave?

699
00:51:11,730 --> 00:51:12,970
She's at a friend's house.

700
00:51:13,860 --> 00:51:15,890
She said she'll be home in a few days.

701
00:51:15,890 --> 00:51:17,860
She said she just felt like leaving.

702
00:51:19,020 --> 00:51:20,790
I'm beginning to hate her.

703
00:51:20,790 --> 00:51:22,740
We were worried sick about her!

704
00:51:22,740 --> 00:51:24,090
I know...

705
00:51:31,020 --> 00:51:33,040
Don't leave anything behind.

706
00:51:33,040 --> 00:51:34,710
Okay.

707
00:51:42,710 --> 00:51:44,050
Why aren't you getting off?

708
00:51:44,050 --> 00:51:45,070
Oh...

709
00:51:47,760 --> 00:51:53,750
Most missing people
end up being runaways.

710
00:51:54,840 --> 00:51:57,670
I'm glad nothing bad happened to her.

711
00:51:57,670 --> 00:52:00,130
I told you that nothing bad will happen.

712
00:52:01,740 --> 00:52:04,050
I don't want to take to Yun-Shil anymore.

713
00:52:04,050 --> 00:52:06,030
We got ourselves into
this mess for nothing.

714
00:52:06,040 --> 00:52:08,910
Maybe she ran away because
she didn't want to clean the trash bin!

715
00:52:08,930 --> 00:52:10,090
Maybe that's why.

716
00:52:10,090 --> 00:52:11,820
Don't you think so too?

717
00:52:11,820 --> 00:52:12,910
Huh?

718
00:52:12,910 --> 00:52:14,130
Yeah...

719
00:52:21,010 --> 00:52:27,980
As soon as we verify the husband's call, the Sokcho station will close the case.

720
00:52:27,980 --> 00:52:29,930
Can you verify it right now?

721
00:52:29,930 --> 00:52:33,720
It'll take a few hours.

722
00:52:33,720 --> 00:52:36,020
Call me if she comes home
before we're done.

723
00:52:36,030 --> 00:52:37,060
Okay.

724
00:52:48,710 --> 00:52:50,780
Hi! Are you done?

725
00:52:51,110 --> 00:52:53,000
What are you doing here?

726
00:52:54,910 --> 00:52:56,080
This is my sister.

727
00:52:56,080 --> 00:52:58,130
She was worried about
Yun-Shil the whole day.

728
00:53:01,050 --> 00:53:04,070
Get in, I'll drive you home.

729
00:53:27,030 --> 00:53:30,780
Thank you for coming on a rainy day.

730
00:53:31,980 --> 00:53:33,930
Thank you.

731
00:53:35,970 --> 00:53:37,920
Let's go and get some food for the kids.

732
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:43,780
Is there a way to erase my phone number from the police files?

733
00:53:44,790 --> 00:53:49,780
Who are you trying to hide from?

734
00:53:50,730 --> 00:53:55,790
No, I'm doing this because I'm
too popular with my good looks.

735
00:53:58,010 --> 00:53:59,860
Anyways, thank goodness it's over.

736
00:53:59,860 --> 00:54:02,150
I'm never going to the beach again.

737
00:54:02,150 --> 00:54:03,800
Bye.

738
00:54:03,800 --> 00:54:08,720
Wait, hold on... I have something
to tell you... hold on.

739
00:54:10,690 --> 00:54:12,800
What's the matter?

740
00:54:15,800 --> 00:54:17,860
Look...

741
00:54:17,860 --> 00:54:19,130
What's this?

742
00:54:21,840 --> 00:54:23,000
Blood!

743
00:54:23,000 --> 00:54:23,900
Get it off me!

744
00:54:23,900 --> 00:54:25,800
I'm scared of blood!

745
00:54:25,800 --> 00:54:26,940
Did you get hurt?

746
00:54:26,940 --> 00:54:28,060
It's not mine.

747
00:54:28,060 --> 00:54:30,000
It's from the white pants
on a rainy day's car.

748
00:54:31,040 --> 00:54:33,690
White pants on a rainy day?

749
00:54:33,690 --> 00:54:34,790
Yun-Shil's husband.

750
00:54:35,960 --> 00:54:41,850
Doesn't this look like the scarf
Yun-Shil had on at the beach?

751
00:54:41,850 --> 00:54:43,100
Don't you remember?

752
00:54:43,100 --> 00:54:44,150
No way...

753
00:54:45,710 --> 00:54:48,760
I think she had a scarf on...

754
00:54:49,690 --> 00:54:52,870
Stop it, you're scaring Su-Duk.

755
00:54:52,870 --> 00:54:56,870
I'm positive she had this scarf on.

756
00:54:56,880 --> 00:54:57,970
You're right!

757
00:54:57,970 --> 00:54:59,120
This is hers!

758
00:54:59,120 --> 00:55:01,830
You're scaring me!

759
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:03,820
Why is there blood on this?

760
00:55:03,820 --> 00:55:06,950
Why is this in the white pants' car?

761
00:55:09,850 --> 00:55:11,790
It's the white pants!

762
00:55:17,700 --> 00:55:20,670
Look at white pants!

763
00:55:27,830 --> 00:55:30,860
That's the woman we just saw!

764
00:55:30,860 --> 00:55:32,730
I thought she was his sister!

765
00:55:32,730 --> 00:55:33,800
Why did he kiss his sister?

766
00:55:34,900 --> 00:55:36,870
She's not his sister.

767
00:55:44,040 --> 00:55:45,810
Where are you guys going?

768
00:55:45,810 --> 00:55:47,770
Wait! Wait!

769
00:55:51,030 --> 00:55:53,000
I thought you said she's your sister.

770
00:55:53,000 --> 00:55:57,970
Ma'am, please don't meddle
in someone else's affairs.

771
00:55:57,970 --> 00:56:00,720
I'm sure you're preoccupied with just taking care of your own family.

772
00:56:00,720 --> 00:56:02,680
Carry on.

773
00:56:02,690 --> 00:56:04,110
I'll be on my way.

774
00:56:05,100 --> 00:56:07,000
Wait!

775
00:56:09,060 --> 00:56:10,150
Yes?

776
00:56:10,150 --> 00:56:13,720
Are you sure you talked to Yun-Shil?

777
00:56:13,720 --> 00:56:15,710
Did she really call?

778
00:56:15,710 --> 00:56:17,690
Tell me the truth.

779
00:56:17,690 --> 00:56:18,910
Yes.

780
00:56:39,890 --> 00:56:41,120
Just pretend you didn't see that.

781
00:56:41,120 --> 00:56:43,060
I don't like meddling in
someone else's business.

782
00:56:44,730 --> 00:56:46,090
What about this?

783
00:56:46,110 --> 00:56:48,010
Do you want to disregard this too?

784
00:56:48,010 --> 00:56:48,940
Yes.

785
00:56:48,940 --> 00:56:50,830
Let's disregard it.

786
00:56:50,830 --> 00:56:51,830
I don't like being scared.

787
00:56:51,830 --> 00:56:53,760
Su-Duk has a weak heart.

788
00:56:54,870 --> 00:56:57,750
What if this really is Yun-Shil's blood?

789
00:56:57,750 --> 00:57:00,090
What if she's in danger? We can't just act as if nothing happened!

790
00:57:00,090 --> 00:57:01,970
You're right.

791
00:57:01,970 --> 00:57:03,760
I'm scared.

792
00:57:03,760 --> 00:57:04,830
Fine, do whatever you want.

793
00:57:04,830 --> 00:57:05,660
Just leave me out.

794
00:57:05,660 --> 00:57:07,150
That's none of my business.

795
00:57:08,100 --> 00:57:10,720
Maybe it's a pig's blood or just red paint.

796
00:57:10,720 --> 00:57:14,860
I don't care if white pants
kissed his sister or a pig.

797
00:57:15,990 --> 00:57:18,800
I don't know anyone from this neighborhood anyway.

798
00:57:18,800 --> 00:57:21,780
I want to keep it that way.

799
00:57:22,140 --> 00:57:23,970
Same here.

800
00:57:24,800 --> 00:57:25,790
You're right.

801
00:57:25,790 --> 00:57:28,030
We shouldn't get ourselves involved.

802
00:57:28,030 --> 00:57:31,930
If she's in danger,
then her husband should help her.

803
00:57:31,930 --> 00:57:34,840
Yes, but look,

804
00:57:34,840 --> 00:57:37,830
He doesn't seem worried at all.

805
00:57:37,830 --> 00:57:40,090
He's even cheating on her.

806
00:57:40,100 --> 00:57:43,960
If Yun-Shil really is in danger,
who's going to help her?

807
00:57:47,970 --> 00:57:49,800
She's by herself.

808
00:57:51,980 --> 00:57:54,690
Right this way.

809
00:57:54,690 --> 00:57:55,920
That's the master bedroom, right?

810
00:57:57,740 --> 00:57:59,860
Call me if you need anything.

811
00:57:59,860 --> 00:58:00,680
Okay.

812
00:58:00,680 --> 00:58:01,660
Thank you.

813
00:58:01,660 --> 00:58:03,740
Goodnight.

814
00:58:23,770 --> 00:58:24,770
Myung-Pil!

815
00:58:24,770 --> 00:58:26,150
Again?

816
00:58:26,150 --> 00:58:27,810
Myung-Pil...

817
00:58:28,750 --> 00:58:29,000
Tae-ran!

818
00:58:29,000 --> 00:58:31,120
Myung-Pil! Myung-Pil!

819
00:58:31,120 --> 00:58:32,140
Get the phone!

820
00:58:32,140 --> 00:58:34,070
No!

821
00:58:34,070 --> 00:58:36,880
Get the phone! Now!

822
00:58:43,020 --> 00:58:44,800
Hello?

823
00:58:44,800 --> 00:58:46,890
Yes, this is Hur Myung-Pil.

824
00:58:49,060 --> 00:58:51,040
The Police?

825
00:58:54,000 --> 00:58:57,840
How can you do this to me?

826
00:58:57,840 --> 00:59:00,050
I'm a law-abiding citizen.

827
00:59:00,050 --> 00:59:01,850
This is too much for me to handle.

828
00:59:01,850 --> 00:59:03,850
What about this scarf?

829
00:59:04,920 --> 00:59:10,750
Tell me why this scarf
was found in your car.

830
00:59:10,750 --> 00:59:12,770
How many times do I have to tell you?

831
00:59:12,770 --> 00:59:14,710
I've never seen that before!

832
00:59:18,070 --> 00:59:21,810
Are you sure you found this in his car?

833
00:59:21,810 --> 00:59:22,800
Yes.

834
00:59:37,990 --> 00:59:39,090
I'm sure.

835
00:59:39,090 --> 00:59:41,140
I found this on the back seat floor.

836
00:59:41,140 --> 00:59:47,030
Look I can get you
imprisoned for slandering!

837
00:59:49,680 --> 00:59:53,830
Don't you have anyone to verify
where you were that night?

838
00:59:53,830 --> 00:59:55,930
I slept at home!

839
00:59:55,930 --> 00:59:58,080
How can I prove that I went to bed?

840
00:59:58,080 --> 01:00:02,730
You're going to regret
that you did this to me.

841
01:00:04,030 --> 01:00:05,840
And you!

842
01:00:11,080 --> 01:00:13,690
I found a lawyer.

843
01:00:13,690 --> 01:00:15,800
Get ready to go to jail.

844
01:00:15,810 --> 01:00:18,110
Calm down...

845
01:00:19,930 --> 01:00:21,150
The file's here.

846
01:00:25,010 --> 01:00:29,860
Seoul 02TA8025.

847
01:00:29,860 --> 01:00:31,090
Is that your license plate number?

848
01:00:33,720 --> 01:00:34,730
Yes.

849
01:00:35,780 --> 01:00:38,720
You went to Sokcho
on the day of the case!

850
01:00:40,130 --> 01:00:42,780
You were caught on speed camera.

851
01:00:42,780 --> 01:00:43,850
Sokcho...

852
01:00:43,850 --> 01:00:45,680
That's where we went.

853
01:00:46,690 --> 01:00:48,000
Excuse me sir...

854
01:00:48,000 --> 01:00:51,670
This man... This man,
there's something fishy about him.

855
01:00:52,020 --> 01:00:53,800
He's even cheating on his wife.

856
01:00:53,800 --> 01:00:54,970
I even saw them kiss.

857
01:00:54,970 --> 01:00:57,830
You saw that too, right?

858
01:00:58,100 --> 01:00:59,710
Look here!

859
01:01:00,960 --> 01:01:02,750
What was your name again?

860
01:01:02,750 --> 01:01:03,780
Gyung Guk-Hee?

861
01:01:03,780 --> 01:01:06,000
Okay, Gyung-Guk-Hee!

862
01:01:06,000 --> 01:01:08,850
Why can't you arrest someone
on the spot for slandering?

863
01:01:08,850 --> 01:01:11,050
Gyung Guk-Hee! I'm going to
throw you in prison!

864
01:01:11,050 --> 01:01:11,830
Understand?

865
01:01:11,830 --> 01:01:12,710
Sit down.

866
01:01:12,710 --> 01:01:13,810
What's going on?

867
01:01:18,690 --> 01:01:20,660
I'm a reporter for Joongdong Daily.

868
01:01:21,700 --> 01:01:22,930
I'm also her husband.

869
01:01:27,910 --> 01:01:30,930
Honey, listen to me.

870
01:01:30,930 --> 01:01:31,930
Be quiet!

871
01:01:33,120 --> 01:01:36,080
Why won't you listen to me?

872
01:01:36,080 --> 01:01:37,840
Be quiet and come with me!

873
01:01:39,730 --> 01:01:40,880
Just hear me out!

874
01:01:40,880 --> 01:01:42,740
Listen to me for once, will you?

875
01:01:42,740 --> 01:01:44,740
Let me explain why I'm doing this.

876
01:01:44,740 --> 01:01:46,150
Something horrible is going on!

877
01:01:46,150 --> 01:01:47,120
Be quiet!

878
01:01:48,720 --> 01:01:50,710
Ouch...

879
01:01:50,710 --> 01:01:51,710
Come on...

880
01:01:51,710 --> 01:01:52,950
Ow, that hurts!

881
01:01:55,990 --> 01:01:57,940
Guk-Hee, are you okay?

882
01:01:58,710 --> 01:02:00,670
Who is he?

883
01:02:00,670 --> 01:02:01,870
You and your friends always
get stuck with scoundrels like him...

884
01:02:01,870 --> 01:02:03,790
...whenever you go.

885
01:02:03,790 --> 01:02:05,970
I got a phone call to
come in for the missing girl.

886
01:02:08,960 --> 01:02:11,740
Honey, are you okay?

887
01:02:12,080 --> 01:02:13,660
Honey?

888
01:02:15,690 --> 01:02:16,750
You have a husband?

889
01:02:18,900 --> 01:02:19,930
Who are you?

890
01:02:21,080 --> 01:02:23,070
Oh...

891
01:02:24,120 --> 01:02:26,710
I'm... Guk-Hee's friend.

892
01:02:26,710 --> 01:02:27,370
What?

893
01:02:29,100 --> 01:02:31,080
Friend?

894
